gnu.trove.decorator
Class TLongFloatMapDecorator

java.lang.Object
  java.util.AbstractMap<java.lang.Long,java.lang.Float>
      gnu.trove.decorator.TLongFloatMapDecorator
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Externalizable, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<java.lang.Long,java.lang.Float>
public class TLongFloatMapDecorator
extends java.util.AbstractMap<java.lang.Long,java.lang.Float>
implements java.util.Map<java.lang.Long,java.lang.Float>, java.io.Externalizable, java.lang.Cloneable

Wrapper class to make a TLongFloatMap conform to the java.util.Map API. This class simply decorates an underlying TLongFloatMap and translates the Object-based APIs into their Trove primitive analogs.

Note that wrapping and unwrapping primitive values is extremely inefficient. If possible, users of this class should override the appropriate methods in this class and use a table of canonical values.

Created: Mon Sep 23 22:07:40 PDT 2002
